1 Mentre che sì per l’orlo, uno innanzi altro, 2 ce n’andavamo, e spesso il buon maestro 3 diceami: «Guarda: giovi ch’io ti scaltro»;
4 feriami il sole in su l’omero destro, 5 che già, raggiando, tutto l’occidente 6 mutava in bianco aspetto di cilestro;
7 e io facea con l’ombra più rovente 8 parer la fiamma; e pur a tanto indizio 9 vidi molt’ ombre, andando, poner mente.

query.result:
**English:**
1 While thus along the edge, one in front of the other, 2 we were going, and often the good master 3 said to me: "Look: it is good that I make you wise";
4 the sun was striking me on my right shoulder, 5 which, already shining, was changing all the west 6 into a white aspect of light blue;
7 and I was making the flame appear 8 with the shadow more glowing; and yet by such an indication 9 I saw many shades, walking, taking note.
**Sanskrit:**
